HEADWORD: Lacewing
<hw>Lace"wing`</hw> <pr>(l⟦amac⟧s"w⟦icr⟧ng`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species of neuropterous
insects of the genus <gen>Chrysopa</gen> and allied genera. They have
delicate, lacelike wings and brilliant eyes. Their larv⟦ae⟧ are useful
in destroying aphids. Called also <altname>lace-winged fly</altname>,
and <altname>goldeneyed fly</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lace-winged</ent>⟦br⟧
